  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Sleep-periodic-limb-movement">
    <rdfs:label>Sleep-periodic-limb-movement</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>PLMS. Periodic limb movement in sleep. Episodes are characterized by brief (0.5- to 5.0-second) lower-extremity movements during sleep, which typically occur at 20- to 40-second intervals, most commonly during the first 3 hours of sleep. The affected individual is usually not aware of the movements or of the transient partial arousals.</rdfs:comment>
